449// An ExternalReference represents a C++ address used in the generated
450// code. All references to C++ functions and variables must be encapsulated
451// in an ExternalReference instance. This is done in order to track the
452// origin of all external references in the code so that they can be bound
453// to the correct addresses when deserializing a heap.
454class ExternalReference {
455 public:
456 // Used in the simulator to support different native api calls.
457 enum Type {
458 // Builtin call.
459 // Address f(v8::internal::Arguments).
460 BUILTIN_CALL, // default
461
462 // Builtin call returning object pair.
463 // ObjectPair f(v8::internal::Arguments).
464 BUILTIN_CALL_PAIR,
465
466 // TODO(mslekova): Once FAST_C_CALL is supported in the simulator,
467 // the following four specific types and their special handling
468 // can be removed, as the generic call supports them.
469
470 // Builtin that takes float arguments and returns an int.
471 // int f(double, double).
472 BUILTIN_COMPARE_CALL,
473
474 // Builtin call that returns floating point.
475 // double f(double, double).
476 BUILTIN_FP_FP_CALL,
477
478 // Builtin call that returns floating point.
479 // double f(double).
480 BUILTIN_FP_CALL,
481
482 // Builtin call that returns floating point.
483 // double f(double, int).
484 BUILTIN_FP_INT_CALL,
485
486 // Builtin call that returns floating point.
487 // double f(Address tagged_ptr).
488 BUILTIN_FP_POINTER_CALL,
489
490 // Direct call to API function callback.
491 // void f(v8::FunctionCallbackInfo&)
492 DIRECT_API_CALL,
493
494 // Direct call to accessor getter callback.
495 // void f(Local<Name> property, PropertyCallbackInfo& info)
496 DIRECT_GETTER_CALL,
497
498 // C call, either representing a fast API call or used in tests.
499 // Can have arbitrary signature from the types supported by the fast API.
500 FAST_C_CALL
501 };
